               <history>
                  <origin><origPlace>(Byzantium)</origPlace>
                     <origDate when="1337" calendar="Gregorian">1337. Date from colophons. Part 1
                        finished 25 Nisan (50)97, part 2 finished 2 Iyar (50)97 and part 3 finished
                        14 Iyar (50)97 = 1337.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance> Ownership inscriptions: Elijah ben Abba Delmedigo, who bought it from
                     Aaron ben Jacob Tsarfati on 6 Tevet 5191 = 1430. Jacob ben Abraham Rintel in
                     Berlin. </provenance>
                  <provenance> <persName role="fmo">Aaron ben Jacob Tsarfati</persName></provenance>
                  <provenance> <persName role="fmo">Elijah ben Abba Delmedigo</persName></provenance>
                  <provenance><persName role="fmo">Frenḳil Teʾomim, Yehuda Ary. Leybush</persName></provenance>
                  <provenance><persName role="fmo"> Michael Simeon of Breslau</persName></provenance>
                  <provenance><persName role="fmo" key="person_17140230">Michael, Heimann Joseph, 1792-1846</persName></provenance>
                  <provenance><persName role="fmo">Rintel, Jacob ben Abraham</persName></provenance>

                  <provenance>The first edition of the third item, the Tosafot on tractate Eduyot,
                     was published under the title עדות נאמנה in Dessau (1813) based on this
                     manuscript; the editor, Judah Aryeh Fränkel Löbusch Teomim, wrote that he
                     purchased the manuscript from Michael Simeon of Breslau (Wrocław).</provenance>

                  <acquisition>It belonged to the library of Heimann Joseph Michael (1792-1846),
                     which was purchased en bloc (altogether 862 manuscript volumes) by the Bodleian
                     Library in 1848 through Messrs. Asher and Co. for £1030.</acquisition>
               </history>
